{"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"],"fields":{"title":{"boost":1000.0},"text":{"boost":1.0},"tags":{"boost":1000000.0}}},"docs":[{"location":"","title":"Applied AI Engineering Handbook","text":"<p>This handbook documents my journey toward becoming a production-ready Applied AI Engineer.</p> <p>Topics include:</p> <ul> <li>Backend Engineering</li> <li>AI Systems</li> <li>RAG</li> <li>Cloud Infrastructure</li> <li>Docker</li> <li>GCP</li> <li>Software Architecture</li> <li>AI Agents</li> <li>Production Systems</li> </ul>"},{"location":"#current-learning-path","title":"Current Learning Path","text":""},{"location":"#layer-1-software-engineering-foundations","title":"Layer 1 \u2014 Software Engineering Foundations","text":"<ul> <li>Python Engineering</li> <li>Git &amp; GitHub</li> <li>Project Structure</li> <li>Software Architecture</li> </ul>"},{"location":"#layer-2-backend-engineering","title":"Layer 2 \u2014 Backend Engineering","text":"<ul> <li>HTTP</li> <li>APIs</li> <li>Authentication</li> <li>Databases</li> <li>Business Logic</li> </ul>"},{"location":"#layer-3-ai-engineering","title":"Layer 3 \u2014 AI Engineering","text":"<ul> <li>LLMs</li> <li>RAG</li> <li>Vector Databases</li> <li>Agents</li> </ul>"},{"location":"#goal","title":"Goal","text":"<p>Become a production-ready Applied AI Engineer with strong backend, cloud, and AI systems knowledge.</p>"},{"location":"backend/http/","title":"HTTP Basics","text":""},{"location":"backend/http/#what-is-http","title":"What is HTTP?","text":"<p>HTTP = HyperText Transfer Protocol</p> <p>It is the communication protocol between:</p> <ul> <li>Frontend</li> <li>Backend</li> <li>APIs</li> <li>Browsers</li> <li>AI services</li> </ul>"},{"location":"backend/http/#why-http-matters","title":"Why HTTP Matters","text":"<p>Modern applications communicate using HTTP.</p> <p>Example:</p> <p>Frontend \u2192 Backend Mobile App \u2192 API AI Service \u2192 Backend</p>"},{"location":"backend/http/#http-is-stateless","title":"HTTP is Stateless","text":"<p>Each request is independent.</p> <p>The server does not automatically remember previous requests.</p>"},{"location":"backend/http/#common-http-methods","title":"Common HTTP Methods","text":""},{"location":"backend/http/#get","title":"GET","text":"<p>Retrieve data.</p> <p>Example:</p> <p>GET /users</p>"},{"location":"backend/http/#post","title":"POST","text":"<p>Send data.</p> <p>Example:</p> <p>POST /chat</p>"},{"location":"backend/http/#put-patch","title":"PUT / PATCH","text":"<p>Update data.</p>"},{"location":"backend/http/#delete","title":"DELETE","text":"<p>Delete data.</p>"},{"location":"backend/http/#request-structure","title":"Request Structure","text":"<p>An HTTP request usually contains:</p> <ul> <li>Method</li> <li>URL</li> <li>Headers</li> <li>Body</li> </ul> <p>Example:</p> <p>Authorization: Bearer JWT_TOKEN</p>"},{"location":"backend/http/#response-structure","title":"Response Structure","text":"<p>A response usually contains:</p> <ul> <li>Status code</li> <li>Headers</li> <li>JSON data</li> </ul> <p>Example:</p> <p>{   \"message\": \"Success\" }</p>"},{"location":"backend/http/#important-status-codes","title":"Important Status Codes","text":""},{"location":"backend/http/#200-ok","title":"200 OK","text":"<p>Success.</p>"},{"location":"backend/http/#201-created","title":"201 Created","text":"<p>Resource created successfully.</p>"},{"location":"backend/http/#400-bad-request","title":"400 Bad Request","text":"<p>Client error.</p>"},{"location":"backend/http/#401-unauthorized","title":"401 Unauthorized","text":"<p>Authentication required.</p>"},{"location":"backend/http/#403-forbidden","title":"403 Forbidden","text":"<p>Authenticated but not allowed.</p>"},{"location":"backend/http/#404-not-found","title":"404 Not Found","text":"<p>Resource not found.</p>"},{"location":"backend/http/#500-internal-server-error","title":"500 Internal Server Error","text":"<p>Backend/server issue.</p>"},{"location":"backend/http/#why-http-matters-for-ai-systems","title":"Why HTTP Matters for AI Systems","text":"<p>AI applications rely heavily on APIs and HTTP communication.</p> <p>Examples:</p> <ul> <li>Chat APIs</li> <li>Embedding APIs</li> <li>Authentication services</li> <li>AI gateways</li> </ul>"},{"location":"backend/jwt/","title":"JWT","text":""},{"location":"backend/jwt/#problem","title":"Problem","text":"<p>HTTP is stateless.</p>"},{"location":"backend/jwt/#traditional-solution","title":"Traditional Solution","text":"<p>Sessions.</p>"},{"location":"backend/jwt/#problem-with-sessions","title":"Problem with Sessions","text":"<p>Hard to scale in cloud systems.</p>"},{"location":"backend/jwt/#modern-solution","title":"Modern Solution","text":"<p>JWT.</p>"},{"location":"backend/jwt/#why-jwt-is-stateless","title":"Why JWT is Stateless","text":"<p>The server does not store authentication session state. The token itself contains the information.</p>"},{"location":"backend/jwt/#why-this-matters-for-ai-systems","title":"Why This Matters for AI Systems","text":"<p>AI APIs need scalable authentication systems.</p>"}]}